Author: harosho
Title: [ICO][Airdrop] StockBlock - Copyright protection & Marketplace for Media Artist
Body: I believe in developers. But not in this ones I used to be a developer myself .. and what I see is a bunch of bullshit.  Quote from: stockblock on November 20, 2017, 05:35:10 PM The important part here is the platform. The algorithm works on our alpha release... The UI is temporary and will be updated/upgraded in final release. We are trying to solve a real problem. Have a look at the whitepaper for more info. The media can be stored anywhere. We are looking for alternative like ipfs storage etc.  Which problem are you solving? There are many platforms like this on the internet. OK, they don't use the all-mighty buzz word "blockchain", but they function as one should. It seems you don't understand the meaning of "alpha" stage. That's the first step towards the final product - not just a temporary solution to make people excited and investors pleased. I don't know if you actually know how ipfs works - yes, data is stored on the "Distributed Web", but you'll have to make it accessible via HTTP (who else will use your application). You could use any storage, doesn't solve any problem. It's clear, you don't have a clue what you are doing and how you'll realise your idea .. and therefor it is a shit coin.

Author: QlooQl
Title: [ICO][Airdrop] StockBlock - Copyright protection & Marketplace for Media Artist
Body: Interesting angle. Copyright could benefit from the blockchain. The first person to post a creative idea, picture, story, etc on the blockchain would have copyright over that idea. So instead of needing a government agency to hold all the paperwork the blockchain does that part for people. Anyone, like a lawyer can look back at the posted info available freely to everyone and decide the merit of a copyright infringement case. This could be a very interesting and even cross-borders alternative to individual countries and their bureaucratic regimes. Good luck with your project!

Author: stockblock
Title: [ICO][Airdrop] StockBlock - Copyright protection & Marketplace for Media Artist
Body: Some photographers rely solely on the concept that they own the copyright when the image is created but then fail to register it with the Copyright Office. When an image is not registered the photographer has just limited the amount she/he can recover for any infringement and may also not be able to recover attorney fees.  Its difficult to prove ownership. Blockchain helps in creating proof-of-ownership. The ability to secure copyright information on the blockchain is ideal. Once the information is registered, it cannot be altered. Therefore, a creator always receives credit without any possibility of dispute and provides you with a “proof of publishing”. Artists can track the activity of their work along with transparent sales and prevent copyright infringement.  With the development of this project along with the marketplace, StockBlock is here to put the power back in the hands of the artists.

Author: stockblock
Title: [ICO][Airdrop] StockBlock - Copyright protection & Marketplace for Media Artist
Body: Hey Carol,  Most of the revenue will be generated via commissions through services. The marketplace will have the usual artwork sales. We also plan to provide auction services. Most of these will earn commissions from 15-40% of the sales. The generated revenue will be used to keep the platform running.  The major income will be from the artwork monitoring service. It will be a standalone service that will be integrated into the platform. The artist can opt-in for legal; services. If there is any infringement, the artist can hire the in-house legal team to take care of the infringement. This service will be offered for 40-50% of the total infringement amount received. The in-house team will manage a network of legal entities around the world.  This will help the artist in being more creative rather than managing sales, legal hassles etc. We will take care of everything else.

Author: stockblock
Title: [ICO][Airdrop] StockBlock - Copyright protection & Marketplace for Media Artist
Body: 6 reasons to invest in StockBlock StockBlock solves a century-old copyright infringement problem for media artists. StockBlock empowers a media artist with copyright protection and provides first ever marketplace to securely sell digital art online using Ethereum BlockChain and SmartContracts.  1) A project that helps & honors media artists. Media artist plays an important role in our daily lives. They help us smile, inspire, lift our feelings, freshen up our moods with images, music, movies and more. Millions of such artwork are shared in commercials and online through social media. Do you know where the image or video came from? Who the author is or did he get compensated for it or even got credited for his work? StockBlock is here to help such artists earn a livelihood and be honored with credits & attribution.  2) You like investing in a project with higher chance of value in future. The platform helps media artists fight for their rights and also helps them in making a better living. Based on the trust and value proposition, the project is likely to excel in business worldwide. We are narrowing our focus to photography until our beta release. With expansion into various digital assets like videos, music, the expected project growth multi folds along with greater returns for your investments.  3) StockBlock is here to disrupt the media industry. If the media industries were to embrace blockchain technologies, they could reduce costs for distribution, royalty and licensing collection and allow consumers to obtain the content they want and are willing to pay for. Photos could be recorded on the ledger immutably, with their copyrights protected and their creators confirmed.  4) Worlds First Marketplace platform using blockchain for media artist. Current stock photography websites pay peanuts to the very artist who creates content for these agencies. These agencies are nothing without the artist artwork. Agencies earn over 70% of revenues generated selling the artwork. StockBlock is here to end this centralized intermediaries and provide better living standards for the artist.  5) StockBlock ICO investment at the lowest price. With blockchain innovation and ICO, it is now feasible to raise operating capital. StockBlock is a much-needed project to solve real-life issues of media artists. We look forward to making this a reality with your support. Our StockBlock ICO offers the lowest price for our tokens to invest in. Anyone can join and support our cause and make this project a reality.  6) Alpha release — Proof-of-concept We have alpha release with proof of concept. Please visit http://alpha.stockblock.io Screenshot of the platform.       Please check the website for more information. WebSite: http://stockBlock.io StockBlock Pre-ICO & ICO: http://stockblock.io/ico.html

Author: stockblock
Title: [ICO][Airdrop] StockBlock - Copyright protection & Marketplace for Media Artist
Body: What is OP?  The project is all about Copyright protection and Marketplace for media artist. Initially, the platform will be for photographers & illustrators (Images mainly). The platform will be extended to other digital assets like music and videos.  How copyright protection works:  Currently, none of the stock photography websites offer copyright solution to the photographers(Artist). If the images are stolen, there's no proof of ownership. It's difficult to prove the image ownership unless you have legally registered the image with the government. Unfortunately, the registrars don't do much beyond registering your images. For photographers, its financially not possible to legally register and pay for thousands of images.  This is where blockchain comes in. The ability to securely store copyright information on the blockchain is ideal. Once the information is registered, it cannot be altered. All of this can be done using SmartContracts. The SmartContract can also receive payments for the images or any artwork that is for sale.   Secondly, all payments received by the contracts are final with no scope of reversing the payments. The artist receives the payment instantly.  Along with copyright information, we will also provide a monitoring system for images. The artist will be able to track who uses their images, who bought it and everything in between. The true power of using decentralized blockchain system.  We have released an alpha version of the platform: http://alpha.stockblock.io  The images used on the alpha version are random images. It has nothing to do with medicine.

Author: stockblock
Title: [ICO][Airdrop] StockBlock - Copyright protection & Marketplace for Media Artist
Body: Hi,  The system uses perceptual hashing to identify similar images. Please check our algorithm test page: https://stockblock.io/fingerprint/  The system uses perceptual hash/ Fingerprint to identify an image. The system can identify images even after the image has been seriously altered. The similarity score defines how similar the image is. So similarity score above 90 is the same image.  This fingerprint is used to find duplicates in the platform itself. The same fingerprint is used to find/monitor the images on the internet. The monitoring system will be a background process. The system will crawl the internet and find images and report the same to the photographers monitoring dashboard. The photographer can decide what actions need to take regarding the infringement.

Author: stockblock
Title: [ICO][Airdrop] StockBlock - Copyright protection & Marketplace for Media Artist
Body: Good to know you are an artist.  There are 2 contracts mainly.  For proof of ownership. All info regarding the author/artist goes on blockchain.  Full Name State, City Country StockBlock Artist ID(Unique) Image Hash/Fingerprint Copyright Info If any(Legal) URL of the image uploaded on the server/cloud/blockchain  All above details are time-stamped on ethereum blockchain.  Human readable data will be compiled in a PDF format for the artist. Just like a certificate of ownership. The data can also be viewed on etherscan.io. (Read Smart Contract Tab) The ContractABI code will be published for the artwork.  The SmartContract will be owned by StockBlock and The Artist.  A kill function would be implemented just in case the user wants to delete the contract information. Some additional parameters will be added to switch cases as per need.  When the user adds the image in marketplace they might creates editions with price depending on the needs. Those multiple editions will correspond to a new smartcontract for each. The buyers pays for these editions and the status of the transaction is updated and the editions are updated accordingly after transaction confirmations. All transactions of that artwork will be tracked as artwork history.  Thats the basic functionality of the smartcontracts. The artist never pays for the contract creation. It happens in the back-end. All transactions will be batch processed to save gas and stuff.  I am not able to upload images here yet.  This is how it will look.  http://stockblock.io/images/preview1.jpg  http://stockblock.io/images/preview2.jpg  Let me know what you think.

Author: stockblock
Title: [ICO][Airdrop] StockBlock - Copyright protection & Marketplace for Media Artist
Body: Hello FrankNoland,  Thannks for your inputs. I will update the first page project details by tomorrow. I am not able to display images as of now.  Well the project mainly is for media artist. Currently there is no definite solution to solve copyright issues. To explain the issue lets assume a photographer for example.  When a photographer clicks images, he owns the copyright. Its not necessary to register the copyright legally. If you click that shutter you own the copyright. The problem arises when someone steals the image and use it on their website or banner ads etc for commercial or non-commercial purposes. When the photographer files a case or send cease and desist, the photographer needs to prove he owns it. Usually proving ownership is a problem. If you are unable to prove it in court, you lose.  Proof of existence & proof of ownership.  We have selected Ethereum blockchain for the platform. Using ethereum blockchain we create smartcontracts for the artwork. The artworks is registered using image hashing. Precisely perceptual hashing. The artist receives a PDF file with all information regarding the artwork. It is kind of a birth certificate for the artwork. The artwork is time-stamped with copyright and attributes. The platform also provides a marketplace for the artist to sell the artwork. All transactions are done using ERC20 tokens. The entire ecosystem works on this ERC20 Token System ONLY(XMC Tokens).   Total 250,000,000 tokens will exist. That's the max supply. The following wallets are known to be compatible with Ethereum tokens (ERC-20 standard):  MyEtherWallet (no download needed) MetaMask (Firefox and Chrome browser addon) Mist (Desktop) Parity (Desktop)   We are a small team and currently working on the photographers section of the project. We do not have enough resource to allocate for this project. Hence we are looking forward for the ICO. This project has huge potential. This platform can provide solution for photographs, movies, music, illustrations, 3D, documentation and other digital assets. For investors its a great opportunity. We have soft cap of 25,000 Ether and Hard Cap of 75,000 Ethers. This project is a global solution for various problems.  I will update the same with more detailed information on the first page post and also update our website accordingly.  Thats all for now. I will drop you a msg when I update it all.  Regards, Mangesh

Author: stockblock
Title: [ICO][Airdrop] StockBlock - Copyright protection & Marketplace for Media Artist
Body: Hi,  Both VibeHub and OPUS have different user base. What seperates us from them is the business model. VibeHub is for end users meaning it is B2C. Business to consumer. Whereas StockBlock is B2B business to business.  Photographers sell their artwork to digital agencies, publishing houses, media houses and so on. Primarily the artwork is used in creating advertisement materials like banners, flyers print magazine advertisement. A lot of web agencies use these conceptual images for their websites.  What separates us from the other 2 is we help these media artist register and protect their copyright with attribute on blockchain forever. We time-stamp their artwork preventing them from copyright abuse. The proof of ownership and proof of publishing helps them in fighting for their rights.  This system is being developed to empower the media artist with their rights and be able to monetize their artwork using our marketplace.  We have explained detailed project scope in the whitepaper. The entire StockBlock platform ecosystem is explained in detail. Please have a look at it.

Author: kolesozw
Title: [ICO][Airdrop] StockBlock - Copyright protection & Marketplace for Media Artist
Body: Thank you for the information.  I have just one more question. If you will protect the artists, will you have some algorithm to detect slightly edited image versions of images which are already on the chain or you will just use the chain if somebody manually report copyright violation?

Author: stockblock
Title: [ICO][Airdrop] StockBlock - Copyright protection & Marketplace for Media Artist
Body: That's a very good question. I will be able to elaborate the concept more clearly.  Check this page: http://stockblock.io/fingerprint/ The first image is the original image. Check the other images, the phash value under every image and the similarity score. Anything above 90% is same image.  When a user uploads images, same user can have multiple similar images(altered like blurred, grayscale etc) as the same user owns it. There can not be two same images (similarity score more than 90) in different user accounts. The system checks for similarity score and approves it automatically.  This also helps keeping fraudsters off the system. If someone uploads a stolen image, the account is flagged and a ticket is opened for dispute. The fraudster is flagged for plagiarism. The system search also uses the perceptual hashing system to display the search results.  ➢ Finding similar images (With phash similarity score more than 90%) ➢ Finding visually unique images. (With phash similarity score less than 30%)  The marketplace platform is fraudster-proof. With unique, verified, attributed content, the buyer is assured of buying genuine artwork. To secure the platform further, the registration of artist is invite only. It is a blockchain of trusted media artist.  Storing images:  The images are not stored on the block chain for now. It is very expensive to store images on block chain. But there's are some projects like storj and filecoin with whom we can collaborate and workout some deals instead of creating the entire file storage system ourselves. As of now we are storing the images on cloud server for test purposes.  Does this make sense?  Let me know,

Author: kolesozw
Title: [ICO][Airdrop] StockBlock - Copyright protection & Marketplace for Media Artist
Body: It make sense. I like it.  But I think Flipped V and Flipped H also should generate result over 90 points as it still the same image. Filecoin is a good option. If I recall it correct, they've managed to collect over 250M which is more than enough to make a working infrastructure.

Author: stockblock
Title: [ICO][Airdrop] StockBlock - Copyright protection & Marketplace for Media Artist
Body: Yes. Anything from 30 to 90 similarity goes through next set of algorithm. There will be a couple set of hashes generated for flipped H or V and more.  That is the technical automated moderation.  Finally the moderator checks for quality of the image and approves it.  Once approved, the author can generate editions of the artwork for sale. These will be the actual SmartContracts that buyers will pay for.  The transactions will be transparent and can track the history of the artwork. Who sold it, who bought it, editions, and everything in between. Protection for both buyer and seller to prove their sale and purchase. This info will be displayed on the artwork page. (The buyer chooses privacy options to display info.)  Since the payment is final and no possibility of getting reversed, the author gets paid instantly using the SmartContracts with automated instructions to transfer tokens and commission for the platform.

Author: stockblock
Title: [ICO][Airdrop] StockBlock - Copyright protection & Marketplace for Media Artist
Body: I think storj is the best bet. We host files with them and we buy hardware to rent 50% of the space to storj. Thus cutting down the expense. That ways we get the infrastructure and have local in-house backups. Win-Win situation.

Author: stockblock
Title: [ICO][Airdrop] StockBlock - Copyright protection & Marketplace for Media Artist
Body: Hello eye4bd,  Steemit is for content sharing. StockBlock is for selling and buying artwork(Digital for now). More over its about preventing copyright infringement and attributing the artwork creator for ever. The platform will also track the images and list all websites where the image is being used. The system wont have any duplicate images as it checks the perpetual hash value. No matter how the image is altered it will display the list of altered images.  Check this test page: http://stockblock.io/fingerprint/  Even after altering the image in various forms the system is able to detect the original image. We are working on couple of things like tracking system database, the platform for buying and selling artwork. This project has been side project as we cant work on it full time as we need earn bread butter. We tried for VC funding but none are ready to invest on projects based on blockchain/crypto currencies.  This is a huge project and to even get into alpha we need to get on it full time. Hence we are planning the ICO.  We are a small team with limited resources. The team profile details will be updated soon. There's just too much to do and very little time and resource.  All we can offer is the tokens for the community support right now.
